== Application Startup ==

group Main()
activate Main
    Main->Main: use flag.String() and define the name env for it and provide the default name as dev and provide description message as Environment(dev,qc,uat,prod)
    Main->Main: then assign it to the variable env
    Main->Main: use flag.Parse() which visit the command line terminal and check the input for example go run main.go env=dev like that it parsing it and assign it to the env
    Main->Server: declare a variable app and err and call the InitializeApp function and pass the env to it
    group InitializeApp()
        activate Server
        Server->Config: create a variable cfg and err and call the function LoadConfig() and pass the service name booking-service and the env to it
        group LoadConfig()
            activate Config
                Config->Config: provide the root path of the env file based on the env for example if dev is passed the developer env should be get like that
                alt if godotenv.Load() envFile
                    alt if not exists
                        Config->Config: if envFile is unable to load which means os.IsNotExist(err) then through "env file isnt present continuing without env file"
                    else
                        Config->Config: if any other error is thrown then throw like failed to load envfile like that and return it
                    end
                end
                Config->Config:create a variable config and then use the struct Config{} which have Port, databaseurl,projectroot and the baseurl and define field here by calling the getEnv() function and pass the key value within it for example "PORT",DATABASE_URL,PROJECT_ROOT, and BASE_URL
                group getEnv()
                    alt if the value is not nil
                        Config->Config: use Getenv() and pass the key to it and get the value of each caller if not unable to get then return empty string
                    end
                end
                Config-->Server: return the config and also the nil to the caller
            deactivate Config
        end
        Server -> Logger: NewLogger(LogConfig{Level, LogDir, FileName, ServiceName})
        group NewLogger()
            activate Logger
                Logger -> Logger: os.MkdirAll(logDir)
                Logger -> Logger: os.OpenFile(filePath)
                Logger -> Logger: zap.New(core, AddCaller)
                Logger --> Server: *Logger
            deactivate Logger
        end
        Server->Server: create a variable dbService and use the &database.DBService{}
        Server -> DB:create a variables db and err and call EstablishConnection()function and pass the cfg.DatabaseURL to it
        group EstablishConnection()
            activate DB
            DB->DB: declare a variable dialector with type gorm.Dialector this variable stores which database driver should be used\nfor example sqlite or sqlserver
            alt if strings.HasPrefix()
                DB->DB: use strings.HasPrefix() and check whether the dbURL starts with sqlite:// example sqlite://test.db
                DB->DB: create a variable dbPath and use strings.TrimPrefix() to remove sqlite:// from the URL\nexample sqlite://test.db becomes test.db
                DB->DB: assign sqlite.Open(dbPath) into dialector this prepares the sqlite driver with the database file path
            else if strings.HasPrefix()
                DB->DB: check whether the dbURL starts with sqlserver:// example sqlserver://localhost:1433
                DB->DB: assign sqlserver.Open(dbURL) into dialector\nthis prepares the sqlserver database driver using the provided URL
            else
                DB->DB: if no known prefix is matched then default to sqlserver.Open(dbURL)
                DB->DB: assign sqlserver.Open(dbURL) into dialector this acts as the fallback database driver
            end
            DB->DB: create variables db and err and call gorm.Open() pass the dialector and &gorm.Config{} gorm.Open() establishes the GORM database connection
            alt if err != nil
                DB-->Server: return nil and err this means the database connection creation failed
            end
            DB->DB: create variables sqlDB and err and call db.DB() this converts the GORM database instance into native sql.DB object
            alt if err != nil
                DB-->Server: return nil and err this means unable to extract the native sql.DB instance
            end
            DB->DB: call sqlDB.Ping() Pong() checks whether the database is reachable and alive
            alt if err := sqlDB.Ping(); err != nil
                DB-->Server: return nil and err this means the database server is unreachable or connection failed
            end
            DB->DB: create and return &Db{} assign Gorm field with db assign SqlDb field with sqlDB
            DB-->Server: return &Db{Gorm: db, SqlDb: sqlDB}, nil successful database connection object is returned
           
        end
        Server->DB: create a variable err and call database.AutoMigrate() and pass the db and logger to it
        group AutoMigrate()
            DB->DB: create a variable err and use db.Gorm.AutoMigrate() then add models like Rooms,Customers,Bookings and Booking_rooms/ to it
            alt if err is not nil
                DB->Server: return err to the server shows failed to run migrations and shows internal server 500 to it
            end
            DB-->Server: return nil to the server caller function
        end
        alt if migration failed
            DB-->Server: if unable to connect the db automigrate then through the error and return nil and err
            deactivate DB
            Server-->Main: throw internal server error 500
            Main-->Client:upwards and forwards the error to the client and raise the internal server error 500
        end
        Server->Server: create a variable router and assign mux.NewRouter() to it to use gorrilla mux
        Server->Router: use handlers and call the SetUpRoutes functions in the routes and pass this above router, db, logger and cfg to it
        activate Router
        group SetupRoutes()
            Router->Router: create a variable bookRepo and use repostiory and initialize its NewBookRepository with passing db and logger to it
            Router->Router: create a variable bookService and use services and injects the bookRepo and logger to the NewBookService
            Router->Router: create a variable bookHandler and use NewBookHandler and inject the bookService and logger to it
            Router->Router: create a variable api and setup the router path prefix as "book/api/v1"
            Router->Router: and use api.HandleFunc() and the endpoint as bookings and use the bookHandler.BookRoom and define its method as post
            Router->Router: then again use the same endpoint and register the other functions like GetRooms and CancelRoom to it with the GET method and PATCH method
            deactivate Router
        end
        Server-->Main: assign the filed logger,router,cfg,dbservice with respective field of the Application struct and return it to the main
        alt if recive an err
            Main-->Client: raise standardize error and throw like failed to initialize the app then close the terminal by providing the os.Exit as 1
        end
        Main->Server: call the server.RunServer() and pass the app to it
        alt if err is not nil
            Main-->Client: raise the message like failed to start the server
            deactivate Main
        end
        group GetCorsOptions()
            Server->Server: return the cors options with allowedOrigins, allowed methods and allowedheaders to it
        end
        group RunServer()
            Server->Server: create a variable corsOpts and assign the GetCorsOptions() functions to it
            Server->Server: create a variable handler and bind the corsOpts with the Handler and app.router tell the server like first entering corsmiddleware then register routes and go to handlers
            Server->Server: use http.ListenAndServe() and pass the port number eg: 8080 by using app.config.Port and assign the handler here
        end
        deactivate Server
    end
end

== Booking room request ==

Client -> Handler: POST /api/v1/bookings{name:"Kirthi","age":22,"address":"123 main street","room_id":101,"start_time":"","end_time":,purpose:"project meeting"
activate Client
activate Handler       
group ReserveRoom()
Handler -> Handler: use the function reserveRoom(w,r)
activate Logger
Handler -> Logger: While processing the booking request, the Handler records a log message stating that a room is being reserved.Info("Recieved request to reserve room")
Handler -> Handler: In a ReserveRoom() create a variable req (in this i will pass BookingRequest)
Handler -> Handler: using json.NewDecoder(r.body).Decode(&req) ( takes the data sent by the client (in JSON format), reads it from the request, and converts it into a Go struct (req) so the handler can easily use it)
alt if JSON decode fails
   Handler -> Logger: Error(Failed to decode request body)
   Handler -> Utils: WriteResponse(w, 400, APIResponse{Status: "Error",Code: 400, Message: "Failed to decode the request",Errors: validationErrors, Timestamp: current time})
   activate Utils
    group WriteResponse()
                alt if the content type is empty
                    Utils->Utils: in w.header() get the content type and check it is empty if it is empty
                    Utils->Utils: then set the content type as application/json
                end
                Utils->Utils: pass the status code to w.WriteHeader()
                alt if error in encoding  
                    Utils-->Client: raise the internal server error and forwards it to the client
                    note over Client
                    {
                        code:500,
                        status:"error",
                        message:"Internal server error",
                        data:None,
                        error:{"type": "HandlerException", "details": str(e)},
                        request_id:request_id,
                        timestamp: timestamp,
                    }
                    end note
                end
            end
            Utils --> Client: upward and raise the error to the client
            note over Client
            {
                code:400,
                status:"error",
                message:"Invalid request format",
                data:None,
                error:{"type": "HandlerException", "details": str(e)},
                request_id:request_id,
                timestamp: timestamp,
            }
            end note
        end
        Handler -> Utils: then use ValidateStruct() and pass the request body &req to it to verify it has the valid required field format or not according to the RoomBookRequest dtos
           
                Utils -> Utils: validate.Struct(s) using go-playground/validator
                Utils --> Handler: []Error (empty if valid)
           
        alt if validation errors exist
            Handler -> Utils:  Refer (62) WriteResponse(w, 400, APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"Validation failed"})
            Utils --> Client: raise and forward the error to the client
            note over Client
            {
                "code":400,
                "status":"error",
                "message":"Invalid request format",
                "data":None,
                "error":{"type": "HandlerException", "details": str(e)},
                "request_id":request_id,
                "timestamp": timestamp,
            }
            end note
        end
Handler -> Service : The handler calls ReserveRoom() in the service layer, passing the request data and context, to process the Booking creation (booking) logic and generate a response.
activate Service
Service -> Logger: While processing the booking request, the Service records a log message stating that a room is being reserved.Info("Recieved request to reserve room")
Service -> Service: Defines the ReserveRoom() function in the service, which takes context and booking request as input and returns an API response.
Service  -> Service: The service checks whether the end date comes after the start date before proceeding with the booking.
 alt if req.StartTime is after req.EndTime
            Service -> Handler: Refer (62) WriteResponse(w, 400, APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"Validation failed"})
            Handler -> Utils: Refer (62) WriteResponse(w, 400, APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"Validation failed"})
            Utils --> Client: raise and forward the error to the client
            note over Client
            {
                "code":400,
                "status":"error",
                "message":"Invalid request format",
                "data":None,
                "error":{"type": "HandlerException", "details": str(e)},
                "request_id":request_id,
                "timestamp": timestamp,
            }
            end note
        end
group GetRoomsByIDs

Service -> Repo: GetRoomsByIDs(ctx, req.RoomIDs)
activate Repo
Repo -> Repo: Validate input room IDs
Repo -> DB: Query rooms table using provided RoomIDs
note over DB
r.db.Gorm.WithContext(ctx).
Where("id IN ? AND is_active = ?", roomIDs, true).
First(&rooms).Error
end note

alt if database error occurs
    Repo -> Logger: Log error "GetRoomsByIDs failed" with error details
    Repo -> Service: Return (nil, dtoErr{Code:"INTERNAL_ERROR", Message:"database error"})
else if one or more rooms not found
    Repo -> Logger: Log warning "rooms not found for given IDs"
    Repo -> Service: Return (nil, dtoErr{Code:"NOT_FOUND", Message:"rooms not found"})
else success
    Repo --> Service: Return (rooms, nil)
end

alt if dtoErr != nil
    Service -> Logger: Log error "ReserveRoom: room lookup failed" with dtoErr.Message
    
    alt if dtoErr.Code == "NOT_FOUND"
        Service -> Handler: CreateErrorResponse(404, "one or more rooms not found", dtoErr)
        Handler -> Utils: WriteResponse(w, 404, APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"one or more rooms not found"})
        Utils -> Client: Send HTTP 404 response
        note over Client
        {
            "code": 404,
            "status": "error",
            "message": "one or more rooms not found",
            "data": null,
            "errors": [
                {
                    "message": dtoErr.Message,
                    "code": "NOT_FOUND"
                }
            ]
        }
        end note
    else
        Service -> Handler: CreateErrorResponse(500, "one or more rooms not found", dtoErr)
        Handler -> Utils: WriteResponse(w, 500, APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"one or more rooms not found"})
        Utils -> Client: Send HTTP 500 response
        note over Client
        {
            "code": 500,
            "status": "error",
            "message": "one or more rooms not found",
            "data": null,
            "errors": [
                {
                    "message": dtoErr.Message,
                    "code": "INTERNAL_ERROR"
                }
            ]
        }
        end note
    end
end
end
group CheckRoomAvailability
Service -> Repo:The service calls CheckRoomAvailability(ctx, req.RoomID, req.StartDate, req.EndDate), where ctx is used to control request lifecycle, req.RoomID identifies the room, req.StartDate and req.EndDate define the booking period, and it receives available (a boolean indicating if the room is free) along with dtoErr (error details if any issue occurs).
Repo -> Repo: A variable `count` is initialized to store the number of booking records that match the query conditions (overlapping bookings)
Repo-> DB : Executes a GORM query on booking_rooms joined with bookings to count active bookings for the given room_id where the requested date range overlaps (existing start_date < new end_date and existing end_date > new start_date) to determine room availability.
note over DB
db.Gorm.WithContext(ctx).
Model(&models.Booking{}). 
Where("room_id = ? AND is_active = ? AND start_date < ? AND end_date > ?",roomID, true, endDate, startDate). 
 Count(&count).Error
end note
  
alt if database error occurs
    Repo -> Logger: Logs error "CheckRoomAvailability failed" with roomID and error details
    Repo -> Service : Sends back a failed response (false) with error details (message and error code), indicating that the room availability check encountered a database error and could not be processed successfully.
else 
Repo--> Service: Return (true if count == 0, false otherwise) indicating room availability status
end
alt if availability check returns error (dtoErr != nil)
    Service -> Logger: Log error "ReserveRoom: availability check failed" with roomID and error message
    Service -> Handler: Refer CreateErrorResponse(500, "failed to check room availability", APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"failed to check room availability", Error: dtoErr})
    Handler -> Utils:  Refer (62) WriteResponse(w, 500, APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"Validation failed"})
    Utils -> Client: Forward HTTP 500 error response to the client
    note over Client
    {
        "code": 500,
        "status": "error",
        "message": "failed to check room availability",
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "field": "room_id",
                "message": dtoErr.Message,
                "code": "INTERNAL_ERROR"
            }
        ]
    }
    end note
end
alt if room is not available (!available)

    Service -> Handler: Refer CreateErrorResponse(409, "rooms are already booked for the requested period", APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"one or more rooms are already booked for the requested period", Error: conflict details})
    Handler -> Utils:  Refer (62) WriteResponse(w, 409, APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"one or more rooms are already booked for the requested period"})
    Utils -> Client: Forward HTTP 409 error response to the client
    note over Client
    {
        "code": 409,
        "status": "error",
        "message": " rooms are already booked for the requested period",
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "field": "room_ids",
                "message": "room already booked",
                "code": "CONFLICT"
            }
        ]
    }
    end note
end
group CreateOrGetCustomer()
Service -> Repo: Calls CreateOrGetCustomer() to create or fetch customer details, and checks if any error (dtoErr) is returned
Repo -> Repo: Defines the CreateOrGetCustomer(ctx, customer) method in the repository to handle creating or retrieving customer data and return any error if the operation fails
Repo -> Repo: Initializes an empty customer object to hold customer data fetched from the database when querying by phone number to determine if the customer already exists.
Repo -> DB : Executes a query to find an active customer whose phone number matches the provided value and stores the result in the customer variable; returns any error encountered during the lookup.
note over DB
db.Gorm.WithContext(ctx).
Where("phone_number = ? AND is_active = ?", req.PhoneNumber, true).
First(&customer).Error
end note
Repo -> Service : Returns the retrieved customer data when the database query succeeds (no error), indicating that an existing active customer was found for the given phone number.
Repo -> Repo: Detects that no existing customer record was found for the given phone number, and proceeds to create a new customer record using the request data.
Repo-> DB : Inserts a new customer record into the database with the provided details (name, age, address, phone number) and system metadata fields.
note over DB
db.Gorm.WithContext(ctx).Create(&customer).Error
end note
alt if create customer query fails (err != nil)
    Repo -> Logger: Log error "CreateCustomer failed" with error details
    Repo --> Service: Return (nil, error details) indicating customer creation failure
else 
    Repo--> Service: Return created customer data
end
alt if unexpected database error occurs during CreateOrGetCustomer (err != nil)
    Repo -> Logger: Log error "CreateOrGetCustomer failed" with error details
end
alt if CreateOrGetCustomer returns error (dtoErr != nil)
    Service -> Logger: Log error "ReserveRoom: CreateOrGetCustomer failed" with phone number and error message
    Service -> Handler: Create error response (500, "failed to process customer", error details)
    Handler -> Utils:  Refer (62) WriteResponse(w, 500, APIResponse{Status:"Error", Message:"failed to process customer"})
    Utils -> Client: Forward HTTP 500 error response to the client
    note over Client
    {
        "code": 500,
        "status": "error",
        "message": "failed to process customer",
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "field": "customer",
                "message": dtoErr.Message,
                "code": "INTERNAL_ERROR"
            }
        ]0
    }
    end note
end
end
